Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle, gradual curve. Possible splash of glaze. Rectangular stamp. Clay medium, brown; many small inclusions.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 173, 20). Name Philios. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0017.30.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0626)
